==Chinese==
===Noun===
[[馬]][[子]] (măshàng; ''Simp.'': [[马子]])

====Sense: [[commode]], [[nightstool]], a seat over a [[chamberpot]]====
=====Sources=====
# Found in the public domain [http://www.mandarintools.com/cedict.html CEDICT]
# Corroborated in [http://www.chinesestudies.hawaii.edu/abc/ ABC Chinese-English Comprehensive Dictionary]
=====Etymology=====
Uncorroborated folk etymology: A google search on the terms 馬子 虎子 帝 馬桶 will reveal hundreds of copies of the story of how a Han Dynasty emperor had a commode in the shape of a tiger, termed 虎子 ; a later Tang Dynasty emperor, with [[虎]] (tiger) in his family name, and the commode was renamed 兽子 or 馬子, later evolving into the term 馬桶 for chamberpot.

====Sense: [[girlfriend]]====
=====Sources=====
# Conversation with two native speakers, one Taiwanese; a google search on 馬子 confirms this sense is extremely widespread

